-- Mexico World Cup Captain Rafael Marquez Joins Henry at New York Red Bulls
-- Barry Rothbard
-- 2010-08-02T23:01:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/mexico-world-cup-soccer-captain-marquez-joins-henry-at-new-york-red-bulls.html

          
          
             The New York Red Bulls signed  Rafael Marquez , Mexicoâ€™s 2010 World Cup captain, from Barcelona, the
 Major League Soccer  team said today in a release on its website.  
 Marquez, 31, won four Spanish league championships and two
European Champions League titles during seven years at
Barcelona, where he played primarily as a central defender.  
 Marquez joins the Red Bulls two weeks after 32-year-old
France striker  Thierry Henry  left Barcelona for the New York
team.  
 Marquez has been captain of Mexico since the 2002 World Cup
and has appeared 94 times for his national team.  
